  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "No, a passport is not compulsory to travel on domestic flights within India. For domestic air travel, passengers are typically required to present a valid government-issued photo ID. Accepted forms of ID include:\n\n1. Aadhar card\n2. Voter ID\n3. Driving license\n4. Pan card\n5. Employee ID (from a government organization or a reputed private company)\n6. Student ID (from a recognized educational institution)\n\nHowever, it is always best to check with the airline for their specific identification requirements before traveling, as they may vary.",
